							<td><img src="images/spacer.gif" width="37" height="15" border="0" alt="." /></td>
						  <td width="205">Government programs such as <a href="http://www.aclu.org/privacy/spying/15701res20050308.html">MATRIX</a> and Carnivore are destroying our privacy. We live in a democratic society and government-controlled data systems are a dangerous step toward establishing a 24-hour surveillance society.<br>
</td>
							<td><img src="images/spacer.gif" width="37" height="15" border="0" alt="." /></td>
						  <td width="205">Recently Northwest Airlines provided the names, addresses, travel plans and credit card numbers of its customers to a NASA project in complete violation of its own privacy policy.&nbsp; In another example, JetBlue provided information from over a million of its customers to the Transportation Security Administration, also in violation of its own privacy policy.
</td>
							<td><img src="images/spacer.gif" width="37" height="15" border="0" alt="." /></td>
							<td width="201">Tell Congress to enact privacy laws that protect us from these intrusions into our private lives. <br>
							  <br>
							If you want to protect your personal privacy, <a href="https://secure.aclu.org/site/Advocacy?pagename=homepage&id=195&page=UserAction">take action</a> right now, <a href="http://action.aclu.org/site/Ecard?ecard_id=2183">tell your friends and family</a>, and <a href="https://www.aclu.org/contribute/contribute.cfm?orgid=EA071504&case=union&cid=16
							">join the ACLU</a>.<br>
